        animator.SetTrigger("Attack");  // Attack triggers every frame!
    }
}

phase2.explanation:
Setting a trigger every frame causes the animation to trigger repeatedly.

**The fix:**
```csharp
if (Input.GetButtonDown("Fire1"))  // Only when button is pressed
{
    animator.SetTrigger("Attack");
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Triggers are for one-time events. Only set them when the event happens."
